The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | United chase Blues
                                                                                                                       7                                      United chase Blues
                      
	London: Mid-season pace setters Chelsea will look to build on last weekends 3-0 defeat of Arsenal and put as much distance between themselves and their closest rivals when they visit Manchester City on Saturday.         
	Manchester United, Liverpool and the Gunners will take the field aiming to close the gap on the leaders.         
	United, who trail Chelsea by five points, know they cannot afford any slips at West Ham where they have suffered two defeats in their last three visits.         
	City can put a lid on what manager Mark Hughes describes as hysteria over their poor form when they host Chelsea.City, who have spent more than 200 million ($331.4 million) in the last year in a bid to break out of the shadow of champions United, have drawn seven games in a row to fall away after a strong start to the campaign.         
	Chelsea have won their last five league games, scoring 17 goals and conceding none, although they were knocked out on penalties by Blackburn Rovers in Wednesdays League Cup semis.         
	Liverpool are at Blackburn and looking to make sure their latest morale boost isnt wasted the same way as the last.         
	But the Reds will again be without Spain striker Fernando Torres, who has been out for a month because of a groin injury.         
	Arsenal host Stoke after a pair of 0-3 losses left them 13 points behind leaders Chelsea.           (AGENCIES)                                                                                                                 
